description:
For Rent -- One Foxhole!

Everytime Joe Anderson went out for anything -- he never got it! But the first time he ever did -- he didn't want it!

Combat Package

It didn't seem as if Pvt. Tommy Adams would ever be a front line soldier! But then he got his chance in a way he never expected -- and he fought back in a way the enemy never expected!

Booby Trap Bunk!

From Kasserine Pass to Tunis, PFC. Joe Burke slept in foxholes, on sharp crags, in biting desert sandstorms, and on the floors of ruined villas! But he had a dream! And he was willing to fight to make it come true!

Fighter Escort (Text only story)

Tank Trouble!

The tank was on its way back to its base -- but then it got into a scrap and before it was over, it had to fight as no tank ever did!

description:
Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Escaped from Castle Morte!
  • My Strangest Manhunt
  • I Was a Jungle Ringmaster!

I Escaped from Castle Morte

Thrill hunter, Allen Travis, is in search of new areas to explore when he comes across Castle Morte. Unfortunately for Travis the castle had become a hideaway for a group of criminals smuggling jewels. These thieves don't take kindly to intruders and it's up to Travis to make a great escape from Castle Morte.

My Strangest Manhunt

Officer Doug Bradley is hired by the U.S. Government to track down a wanted criminal by the name of John R. Harper. Things get strange when Harper saves Bradley's life as the two of them wind up on the run from the true criminals, the mafia!

I Was a Jungle Ringmaster

George and Larry are two friends who want to make it big in the world; however, the only thing they have going for them are George's abilities to tame wild animals. The two of them wind up joining the army where George's talents are put to the test!
name: I Was a Jungle Ringmaster

volume.name: The Adventures of Rex the Wonder Dog

description:
Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Had to Spend a Million!
  • I Raced Death Around the World!
  • I Fought a Live Volcano!

I Had to Spend a Million

Marty Wilson is a down on his luck veteran who can't seem to make a break. Marty's life changes after a mysterious man known as J.J. Dilson contacts Marty and tells him he was great friends with his father and owes him a great deal. Has Marty just struck gold or is there more to this story than Marty sees on the surface?

I Raced Death Around the World

The inter-continental race is one of the most dangerous races in the world. Spanning 20,000 miles the racers must face environmental dangers and road hazards, but how will they fare against unforeseen jewel bandits and gun-toting smugglers?

I Fought a Live Volcano

When the mighty volcano known as Tawoo awakes and becomes live the inhabitants of the island must find some way to defend their island or else it's game over for everyone!
name: I Fought a Live Volcano!
